2:["$","section",null,{"className":"section-space overflow-x-hidden","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"container-main","children":[["$","$L10",null,{"children":["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-6 rounded-3xl border border-brand-100 bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-brand-50/60 p-6 sm:p-8","children":[["$","h1",null,{"className":"mb-4 text-3xl font-black text-slate-900","children":"מאמרים וסרטונים"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-slate-700","children":"תוכן מקצועי מסונן לפי מחלה: מה נבדק, תובנות וקישור למקור."}]]}]}],["$","$L10",null,{"children":["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-8 rounded-3xl bg-[#e7e7e7] p-6 text-center sm:p-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"mb-6 text-3xl font-black text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl","children":"כל המחקרים במקום אחד"}],["$","$L11",null,{"items":[{"id":"fmf-ankinra-acute-attack","titleHe":"טיפול בהתקף חריף: הזרקה מהירה של אנקינרה","titleEn":"Acute Attack Treatment: Fast Anakinra Injection","checkedHe":"מה נבדק במחקר: האם אפשר לעצור התקף FMF בעזרת זריקת בודדת של קינרת?","checkedEn":"What was examined: whether a single Kineret injection can stop an FMF attack.","insightHe":"תובנה למטופל: זריקה בודדת של התרופה הביולוגית אנקינרה (קינרת) שניתנת בזמן, יכולה לעצור את ההתקף ולצמצם משמעותית את הכאב ואת משכו!","insightEn":"Patient insight: a timely single Anakinra (Kineret) injection can stop the attack and significantly reduce pain and duration.","date":"2025-10-01","tags":["FMF","אנקינרה","קינרת"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/41133353/"},{"id":"fmf-v694m-double-mutation","titleHe":"מאפייני מטופלים עם שתי מוטציות V694M","titleEn":"Characteristics of Patients With Double V694M Mutations","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: מה ההשפעה הבריאותית של נשאות כפולה למוטציה V694M","checkedEn":"What was examined: the health impact of double V694M mutation carriage.","insightHe":"תובנה: חולים הומוזיגוטים נמצאים בסיכון למחלה קשה יותר, חוסר תגובה לקולכיצין וסיבוכים. נדרש מעקב קבוע ואיזון מדויק","insightEn":"Insight: homozygous patients have higher risk for severe disease, colchicine non-response, and complications; close monitoring is required.","date":"2025-10-01","tags":["FMF","V694M","גנטיקה"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/40902213/"},{"id":"cutaneous-lupus-plaquenil","titleHe":"פלקווניל בחולי זאבת עורית","titleEn":"Plaquenil in Cutaneous Lupus","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: האם טיפול מוקדם מונע זאבת מערכתית","checkedEn":"What was examined: whether early treatment prevents systemic lupus.","insightHe":"תובנה: טיפול מוקדם מפחית סיכון להתפתחות זאבת מערכתית","insightEn":"Insight: early treatment reduces risk of progression to systemic lupus.","date":"2025-07-01","tags":["לופוס","Plaquenil","זאבת"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/40015570/"},{"id":"jak-inhibitors-gi-perforation-risk","titleHe":"מעכבי JAK וסיכון לנקבים במעי","titleEn":"JAK Inhibitors and Risk of Intestinal Perforation","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: האם יש סיכון לפרפורציות במעי","checkedEn":"What was examined: whether there is risk for intestinal perforation.","insightHe":"תובנה: נמצא דיווח יתר. בחולים עם סיכון למחלת סעיפים במעי צריך לשקול בזהירות","insightEn":"Insight: increased reporting was found; in patients at risk for diverticular disease, treatment should be considered with caution.","date":"2025-05-01","tags":["JAK","מעי","RA"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39736095/"},{"id":"fmf-amyloidosis-followup","titleHe":"מעקב אחר חולי FMF עם עמילואידוזיס","titleEn":"Follow-up of FMF Patients With Amyloidosis","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: האם תפקוד כלייתי נמוך בתחילת האבחנה מנבא אי ספיקת כליות","checkedEn":"What was examined: whether low renal function at diagnosis predicts kidney failure.","insightHe":"תובנה: גילוי מוקדם ומעקב דם ושתן חשובים למניעת אי ספיקת כליות","insightEn":"Insight: early detection and blood/urine follow-up are important to prevent kidney failure.","date":"2025-04-01","tags":["FMF","עמילואידוזיס","כליות"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39908750/"},{"id":"psoriasis-methotrexate-psa-prevention","titleHe":"מתוטרקסט בפסוריאזיס למניעת דלקת מפרקים פסוריאטית","titleEn":"Methotrexate in Psoriasis for PsA Prevention","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: האם טיפול מוקדם עוזר","checkedEn":"What was examined: whether early treatment helps.","insightHe":"תובנה: טיפול מוקדם במתוטרקסט מפחית סיכון לדלקת מפרקים פסוריאטית","insightEn":"Insight: early methotrexate reduces risk of psoriatic arthritis.","date":"2025-03-01","tags":["פסוריאזיס","מתוטרקסט","PsA"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39716640/"},{"id":"feed-4-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39768579","titleHe":"Put Down the ACE: Low Clinical Utility for Angiotensin-Converting Enzyme Levels in Sarcoidosis: A Single-Center Retrospective Cohort Study","titleEn":"Put Down the ACE: Low Clinical Utility for Angiotensin-Converting Enzyme Levels in Sarcoidosis: A Single-Center Retrospective Cohort Study","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: Background/Objectives: ACE (angiotensin-converting enzyme) is considered a serological marker of sarcoidosis as elevated levels have been reported in 30-80% of patients. However, elevated ACE levels are also encountered in other medical conditions, and the clinical correlation between ACE levels and disease activity in sarcoidosis is disputable as well. To determine the significance of elevated ACE levels in the diagnosis and follow-up of sarcoidosis patients. Methods: All electronic patient...","checkedEn":"What was examined: Background/Objectives: ACE (angiotensin-converting enzyme) is considered a serological marker of sarcoidosis as elevated levels have been reported in 30-80% of patients. However, elevated ACE levels are also encountered in other medical conditions, and the clinical correlation between ACE levels and disease activity in sarcoidosis is disputable as well. To determine the significance of elevated ACE levels in the diagnosis and follow-up of sarcoidosis patients. Methods: All electronic patient...","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2025-01-08","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39768579/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"jak-inhibitors-cv-risk-ra","titleHe":"מעכבי JAK ומחלות לב בכל חולי RA","titleEn":"JAK Inhibitors and Cardiovascular Risk in RA","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: האם יש תחלואה קרדיווסקולרית מוגברת","checkedEn":"What was examined: whether cardiovascular morbidity is increased.","insightHe":"תובנה: נמצא דיווח מוגבר. בחולים עם גורמי סיכון צריך לשקול את הסיכון מול התועלת","insightEn":"Insight: increased reporting was found; in patients with risk factors, risk-benefit should be weighed carefully.","date":"2024-08-01","tags":["JAK","RA","קרדיווסקולרי"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38772185/"},{"id":"feed-8-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37792612","titleHe":"Sarilumab for Relapse of Polymyalgia Rheumatica during Glucocorticoid Taper","titleEn":"Sarilumab for Relapse of Polymyalgia Rheumatica during Glucocorticoid Taper","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: CONCLUSIONS: Sarilumab showed significant efficacy in achieving sustained remission and reducing the cumulative glucocorticoid dose in patients with a relapse of polymyalgia rheumatica during glucocorticoid tapering. (Funded by Sanofi and Regeneron Pharmaceuticals; SAPHYR ClinicalTrials.gov number, NCT03600818.).","checkedEn":"What was examined: CONCLUSIONS: Sarilumab showed significant efficacy in achieving sustained remission and reducing the cumulative glucocorticoid dose in patients with a relapse of polymyalgia rheumatica during glucocorticoid tapering. (Funded by Sanofi and Regeneron Pharmaceuticals; SAPHYR ClinicalTrials.gov number, NCT03600818.).","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2023-10-04","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37792612/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"fmf-covid-vaccine-safety","titleHe":"חיסון קורונה בחולי FMF","titleEn":"COVID Vaccine in FMF Patients","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: האם החיסון בטוח לחולי FMF","checkedEn":"What was examined: vaccine safety in FMF patients.","insightHe":"תובנה: החיסון בטוח. חולים עם מחלה פעילה מדווחים על יותר תופעות קלות בלבד","insightEn":"Insight: the vaccine is safe; patients with active disease reported more mild side effects only.","date":"2022-06-28","tags":["FMF","COVID-19","חיסון"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35238382/"},{"id":"feed-9-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35622270","titleHe":"CHA2DS2-VASC Score Predicts the Risk of Stroke in Patients Hospitalized to the Internal Medicine Department Without Known Atrial Fibrillation","titleEn":"CHA2DS2-VASC Score Predicts the Risk of Stroke in Patients Hospitalized to the Internal Medicine Department Without Known Atrial Fibrillation","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: CONCLUSIONS: The CHA2DS2-VASC score is a predictor for CVA/TIA during the first year after hospitalization in patients without AF. High CHA2DS2-VASC scores warrant work-up for occult AF/AFL and other risk factors for CVA/TIA.","checkedEn":"What was examined: CONCLUSIONS: The CHA2DS2-VASC score is a predictor for CVA/TIA during the first year after hospitalization in patients without AF. High CHA2DS2-VASC scores warrant work-up for occult AF/AFL and other risk factors for CVA/TIA.","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2022-05-27","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35622270/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"feed-11-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35094157","titleHe":"The frequency of sacroiliitis on MRI in subjects over 55 years of age","titleEn":"The frequency of sacroiliitis on MRI in subjects over 55 years of age","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: CONCLUSIONS: The frequency of sacroiliitis on SIJs-MRI in subjects > 55 years is similar to its frequency in younger subjects and is associated with the same type and magnitude of active and structural MRI lesions. Clinical parameters such as IBP and additional SpA features are similarly prevalent in older and younger subjects suggesting they suffer from the same disease and differing only in age of presentation.","checkedEn":"What was examined: CONCLUSIONS: The frequency of sacroiliitis on SIJs-MRI in subjects > 55 years is similar to its frequency in younger subjects and is associated with the same type and magnitude of active and structural MRI lesions. Clinical parameters such as IBP and additional SpA features are similarly prevalent in older and younger subjects suggesting they suffer from the same disease and differing only in age of presentation.","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2022-01-30","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35094157/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"fmf-ilaris-after-kineret","titleHe":"תגובה לטיפול באילריס אחרי כישלון קינרת","titleEn":"Response to Ilaris After Kineret Failure","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: האם חולים שלא הגיבו לקינרת יגיבו לאילריס","checkedEn":"What was examined: whether patients who did not respond to Kineret respond to Ilaris.","insightHe":"תובנה: אילריס יעיל גם אחרי כישלון טיפול באנאקינרה. כישלון בתרופה ביולוגית אחת לא שולל הצלחה באחרת","insightEn":"Insight: Ilaris can still be effective after Anakinra failure; failure on one biologic does not rule out success with another.","date":"2021-09-01","tags":["FMF","Ilaris","Kineret"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34369359/"},{"id":"feed-13-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34144604","titleHe":"Anakinra for colchicine refractory familial Mediterranean fever: a cohort of 44 patients","titleEn":"Anakinra for colchicine refractory familial Mediterranean fever: a cohort of 44 patients","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: CONCLUSION: Treatment with anakinra is beneficial for the majority of colchicine-resistant FMF patients and is relatively safe.","checkedEn":"What was examined: CONCLUSION: Treatment with anakinra is beneficial for the majority of colchicine-resistant FMF patients and is relatively safe.","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2021-06-18","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34144604/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"feed-14-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33946748","titleHe":"Immune-Mediated Disease Flares or New-Onset Disease in 27 Subjects Following mRNA/DNA SARS-CoV-2 Vaccination","titleEn":"Immune-Mediated Disease Flares or New-Onset Disease in 27 Subjects Following mRNA/DNA SARS-CoV-2 Vaccination","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: BACKGROUND: Infectious diseases and vaccines can occasionally cause new-onset or flare of immune-mediated diseases (IMDs). The adjuvanticity of the available SARS-CoV-2 vaccines is based on either TLR-7/8 or TLR-9 agonism, which is distinct from previous vaccines and is a common pathogenic mechanism in IMDs.","checkedEn":"What was examined: BACKGROUND: Infectious diseases and vaccines can occasionally cause new-onset or flare of immune-mediated diseases (IMDs). The adjuvanticity of the available SARS-CoV-2 vaccines is based on either TLR-7/8 or TLR-9 agonism, which is distinct from previous vaccines and is a common pathogenic mechanism in IMDs.","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2021-05-05","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33946748/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"feed-15-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33843285","titleHe":"The prevalence of sacroiliitis on abdominal MRI examinations of patients with Takayasu arteritis","titleEn":"The prevalence of sacroiliitis on abdominal MRI examinations of patients with Takayasu arteritis","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: CONCLUSION: Sacroiliitis was detected in 11.7% of abdominal MRI examinations of patients with TA, 75% of which had associated IBD, suggesting that both IBD and sacroiliitis should be routinely screened in the TA population as their presence may influence treatment decisions.","checkedEn":"What was examined: CONCLUSION: Sacroiliitis was detected in 11.7% of abdominal MRI examinations of patients with TA, 75% of which had associated IBD, suggesting that both IBD and sacroiliitis should be routinely screened in the TA population as their presence may influence treatment decisions.","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2021-04-12","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33843285/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"feed-16-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33443348","titleHe":"Ileal Perforation in Granulomatosis with Polyangiitis: A Rare Complication","titleEn":"Ileal Perforation in Granulomatosis with Polyangiitis: A Rare Complication","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: No abstract","checkedEn":"What was examined: No abstract","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2021-01-14","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33443348/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"autoimmune-severe-covid-risk","titleHe":"הסיכון ל COVID קשה בחולים עם מחלות אוטואימוניות","titleEn":"Risk of Severe COVID in Autoimmune Disease","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: האם יש סיכון גבוה יותר למחלה קשה","checkedEn":"What was examined: whether risk for severe COVID is higher.","insightHe":"תובנה: לא נמצא קשר בין מחלה אוטואימונית לסיכון ל COVID קשה","insightEn":"Insight: no association was found between autoimmune disease and severe COVID risk.","date":"2021-01-01","tags":["COVID-19","אוטואימוני"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33277764/"},{"id":"feed-18-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31823531","titleHe":"A CLINICAL DISCUSSION: FEVER OF UNKNOWN ORIGIN IN THE MODERN ERA - MORE QUESTIONS THAN ANSWERS","titleEn":"A CLINICAL DISCUSSION: FEVER OF UNKNOWN ORIGIN IN THE MODERN ERA - MORE QUESTIONS THAN ANSWERS","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: In this case report we discuss a patient who suffers from recurrent bouts of fever and as part of the clinical workup for autoinflammatory diseases was genetically tested for mutations in 26 genes related to autoinflammatory disease with a next generation sequencing test. We discuss the benefits and pitfalls of using this test.","checkedEn":"What was examined: In this case report we discuss a patient who suffers from recurrent bouts of fever and as part of the clinical workup for autoinflammatory diseases was genetically tested for mutations in 26 genes related to autoinflammatory disease with a next generation sequencing test. We discuss the benefits and pitfalls of using this test.","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2019-12-12","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31823531/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"feed-19-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31507107","titleHe":"IS THERE A CORRELATION BETWEEN CARRIAGE OF AN MEFV MUTATION AND GOUT?","titleEn":"IS THERE A CORRELATION BETWEEN CARRIAGE OF AN MEFV MUTATION AND GOUT?","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: CONCLUSIONS: Further large-scale studies should be conducted in order to determine a possible correlation between MEFV mutation carriage and gout.","checkedEn":"What was examined: CONCLUSIONS: Further large-scale studies should be conducted in order to determine a possible correlation between MEFV mutation carriage and gout.","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2019-09-12","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31507107/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"feed-20-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30324790","titleHe":"Diagnosis of Systemic Sclerosis Based on Raynaud's Phenomenon, Capillaroscopy Findings, and Autoantibodies in the Absence of Sclerodactyly","titleEn":"Diagnosis of Systemic Sclerosis Based on Raynaud's Phenomenon, Capillaroscopy Findings, and Autoantibodies in the Absence of Sclerodactyly","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: No abstract","checkedEn":"What was examined: No abstract","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2018-10-17","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30324790/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"feed-21-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29185280","titleHe":"The PET-CT Radiological Appearance of Facial Cosmetic Injections: A Pitfall in the Evaluation of the Oncological Patient","titleEn":"The PET-CT Radiological Appearance of Facial Cosmetic Injections: A Pitfall in the Evaluation of the Oncological Patient","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: CONCLUSIONS: Familiarity with the appearance of such cosmetic procedures on PET-CT is of paramount importance in order to avoid misinterpretation of the findings leading to unnecessary apprehension and work-up.","checkedEn":"What was examined: CONCLUSIONS: Familiarity with the appearance of such cosmetic procedures on PET-CT is of paramount importance in order to avoid misinterpretation of the findings leading to unnecessary apprehension and work-up.","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2017-11-30","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29185280/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"feed-22-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28265433","titleHe":"Return to duty/play after exertional heat injury: do we have all the answers? A lesson from two case studies","titleEn":"Return to duty/play after exertional heat injury: do we have all the answers? A lesson from two case studies","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: CONCLUSION: Susceptibility to heat is a significant determinant for active young people such as athletes and soldiers. Both cases emphasize the importance of the heat tolerance test (and repeated test when needed) as a criteria for an exertional heat related injury patient to return to duty/play and to perform intense physical activities. These cases also emphasize the effectiveness and sensitivity of the test in identifying a temporary and a permanent state of heat intolerance.","checkedEn":"What was examined: CONCLUSION: Susceptibility to heat is a significant determinant for active young people such as athletes and soldiers. Both cases emphasize the importance of the heat tolerance test (and repeated test when needed) as a criteria for an exertional heat related injury patient to return to duty/play and to perform intense physical activities. These cases also emphasize the effectiveness and sensitivity of the test in identifying a temporary and a permanent state of heat intolerance.","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2017-03-08","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28265433/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"feed-23-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27831921","titleHe":"The effects of smoking and nicotine ingestion on exercise heat tolerance","titleEn":"The effects of smoking and nicotine ingestion on exercise heat tolerance","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: CONCLUSIONS: According to this preliminary study, cigarette smoking and nicotine ingestion increase the physiological strain during a HTT in smokers. Acute smoking may, therefore, increase heat intolerance and the risk to heat injuries.","checkedEn":"What was examined: CONCLUSIONS: According to this preliminary study, cigarette smoking and nicotine ingestion increase the physiological strain during a HTT in smokers. Acute smoking may, therefore, increase heat intolerance and the risk to heat injuries.","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2016-11-11","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27831921/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"feed-24-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27612373","titleHe":"Misdiagnosis of Exertional Heat Stroke and Improper Medical Treatment","titleEn":"Misdiagnosis of Exertional Heat Stroke and Improper Medical Treatment","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: No abstract","checkedEn":"What was examined: No abstract","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2016-09-10","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27612373/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"feed-25-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24225520","titleHe":"Recurrent exertional rhabdomyolysis: coincidence, syndrome, or acquired myopathy?","titleEn":"Recurrent exertional rhabdomyolysis: coincidence, syndrome, or acquired myopathy?","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: The purposes of this report are to review and discuss the issue of recurrent exertional rhabdomyolysis (ER), the return to physical activity after ER, and the possible causes of recurrence, with special consideration to metabolic myopathies and the possibility of an acquired post-ER myopathy. We discuss the medical investigation required prior to return to physical activity after an episode of ER and suggest two possible mechanisms for recurrence of ER in the absence of a known cause: premature...","checkedEn":"What was examined: The purposes of this report are to review and discuss the issue of recurrent exertional rhabdomyolysis (ER), the return to physical activity after ER, and the possible causes of recurrence, with special consideration to metabolic myopathies and the possibility of an acquired post-ER myopathy. We discuss the medical investigation required prior to return to physical activity after an episode of ER and suggest two possible mechanisms for recurrence of ER in the absence of a known cause: premature...","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2013-11-15","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24225520/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"feed-26-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23478560","titleHe":"Exertional heat illness: the role of heat tolerance testing","titleEn":"Exertional heat illness: the role of heat tolerance testing","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: Exertional heat stroke (EHS) is a common clinical problem for both athletes and warriors; however, evidence-based guidance for return-to-play/duty (RTP/RTD) decisions is limited. Heat tolerance testing (HTT) has been proposed as a potential tool that, when combined with appropriate clinical information, may assist in RTP/RTD decisions. However, currently, no standard of care is available for performing HTT. The Israeli Defense Forces (IDF) HTT protocol, which was developed over decades of...","checkedEn":"What was examined: Exertional heat stroke (EHS) is a common clinical problem for both athletes and warriors; however, evidence-based guidance for return-to-play/duty (RTP/RTD) decisions is limited. Heat tolerance testing (HTT) has been proposed as a potential tool that, when combined with appropriate clinical information, may assist in RTP/RTD decisions. However, currently, no standard of care is available for performing HTT. The Israeli Defense Forces (IDF) HTT protocol, which was developed over decades of...","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2013-03-13","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23478560/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"feed-27-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23378525","titleHe":"The effect of air permeability characteristics of protective garments on the induced physiological strain under exercise-heat stress","titleEn":"The effect of air permeability characteristics of protective garments on the induced physiological strain under exercise-heat stress","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: CONCLUSIONS: The results emphasize the importance of air permeability in reducing the physiological strain induced by CPCs.","checkedEn":"What was examined: CONCLUSIONS: The results emphasize the importance of air permeability in reducing the physiological strain induced by CPCs.","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2013-02-05","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23378525/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"feed-28-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22986477","titleHe":"Comments to \"Rhabdomyolysis in the US Active Duty Army, 2004-2006\"","titleEn":"Comments to \"Rhabdomyolysis in the US Active Duty Army, 2004-2006\"","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: No abstract","checkedEn":"What was examined: No abstract","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2012-09-19","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22986477/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"feed-29-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22614224","titleHe":"Heat injury prevention--a military perspective","titleEn":"Heat injury prevention--a military perspective","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: Heat-related injuries, and specifically exertional heat stroke, are a significant occupational risk in the armed forces, especially for those soldiers who are rapidly deployed from a temperate climate region to hot climate regions. Traditionally, adaptation to heat was considered as a matter of physiological adaptation. It is clear today that these injuries are mostly avoidable when applying proper education and behavioral adaptations. Education on behavioral adaptation for the prevention of...","checkedEn":"What was examined: Heat-related injuries, and specifically exertional heat stroke, are a significant occupational risk in the armed forces, especially for those soldiers who are rapidly deployed from a temperate climate region to hot climate regions. Traditionally, adaptation to heat was considered as a matter of physiological adaptation. It is clear today that these injuries are mostly avoidable when applying proper education and behavioral adaptations. Education on behavioral adaptation for the prevention of...","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2012-05-23","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22614224/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"feed-30-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22272518","titleHe":"Heat tolerance in women--reconsidering the criteria","titleEn":"Heat tolerance in women--reconsidering the criteria","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: CONCLUSIONS: Using the standard HTT criteria, women are more frequently diagnosed as heat intolerant than men. Further studies should be performed in order to re-evaluate the normal values for a \"female HTT\" in order to optimize the process of safe return to duty of female heat injury victims and to minimize false positive results among female soldiers.","checkedEn":"What was examined: CONCLUSIONS: Using the standard HTT criteria, women are more frequently diagnosed as heat intolerant than men. Further studies should be performed in order to re-evaluate the normal values for a \"female HTT\" in order to optimize the process of safe return to duty of female heat injury victims and to minimize false positive results among female soldiers.","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2012-01-26","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22272518/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"},{"id":"feed-31-https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22165656","titleHe":"Misdiagnosis of exertional heat stroke and improper medical treatment","titleEn":"Misdiagnosis of exertional heat stroke and improper medical treatment","checkedHe":"מה נבדק: Exertional heat stroke (EHS) is the most complicated and dangerous amongst heat injuries that can lead to irreversible injury and even death. Early diagnosis and treatment are therefore crucial determinants of the patient's prognosis. The following case report depicts a soldier who presented primarily with confusion and behavioral changes during physical exercise and later lost consciousness. He was misdiagnosed by the field physician as suffering from supraventricular tachycardia, was treated...","checkedEn":"What was examined: Exertional heat stroke (EHS) is the most complicated and dangerous amongst heat injuries that can lead to irreversible injury and even death. Early diagnosis and treatment are therefore crucial determinants of the patient's prognosis. The following case report depicts a soldier who presented primarily with confusion and behavioral changes during physical exercise and later lost consciousness. He was misdiagnosed by the field physician as suffering from supraventricular tachycardia, was treated...","insightHe":"תובנה: למידע המלא והמדויק יש לפתוח את המחקר המלא ב-PubMed.","insightEn":"Insight: open the full study on PubMed for complete details.","date":"2011-12-15","tags":["פאבמד"],"externalLink":"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22165656/?utm_source=Other&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=pubmed-2&amp;utm_content=107QS1L1jrYfSgKA6801STC9ZPIp31Z_y_WV7b0UZ3k3kdggnA&amp;fc=20241213144035&amp;ff=20260304072758&amp;v=2.19.0.post6+133c1fe"}],"locale":"he"}]]}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-8 space-y-4","children":[["$","$L10",null,{"c